# Global Coding Standards

## TypeScript

- Use TypeScript strict mode patterns; avoid `any` type
- Prefer `const` arrow functions with explicit types over `function` declarations
- Use `@/*` path aliases for imports (configured in tsconfig)

## Code Style

- Use early returns for improved readability
- Use descriptive variable and function names

